Release Notes: RAP v5.1.8

v5.1.8 - released February 21, 2023
* Script changes required to use the new naming convention for the VIIRS fire data input
   * The format and content of the VIIRS fire data remains the same, but the name of the file was changed.  Therefore, the ex-script needs to be modified in order to read in the correct file names.


* Repository Details
   * Clone the rap.v5.1.8 branch of the RAP GitHub repository using the following command (contains v5.1.8 release notes):
* git clone -b rap.v5.1.8 https://github.com/NOAA-EMC/RAP.git


* scripts files changed
   * scripts/exrap_prep_smoke.sh


* resource changes
   * N/A


* implementation instructions
   * Retrieve the rap.v5.1.8 branch from GitHub and update the exrap_prep_smoke.sh script
   * Run a single prep_smoke job.  A full cycle test is not needed.
